# Parallel Function Suffix

Use `_par` suffix for parallel variants of functions, not `_parallel`.

## Bad Examples

```rust
fn map_parallel<F>(a: &Seq<T>, f: F) -> Seq<U> { ... }
fn reduce_parallel<F>(a: &Seq<T>, f: F, id: T) -> T { ... }
fn neighbors_parallel<V>(g: &Graph<V>, v: V) -> Set<V> { ... }
```

## Good Examples

```rust
fn map_par<F>(a: &Seq<T>, f: F) -> Seq<U> { ... }
fn reduce_par<F>(a: &Seq<T>, f: F, id: T) -> T { ... }
fn neighbors_par<V>(g: &Graph<V>, v: V) -> Set<V> { ... }
```

## Rule

The `_par` suffix is shorter and follows common Rust conventions (e.g., Rayon uses `par_iter`). All parallel function variants in APAS use this suffix consistently.
